<br>
<br>
  Truth is vital to me as well.  I am speaking so much of love in order to balance out your truth.  I believe that God represents truth through his actions in the old testament whereas Jesus is love in the new testament.  In many ways we represent God in that(generally speaking) Man represents truth and women represents love.  The unity of the two creates truthly love and lovely truth(ideally).  This is also symbolic in that the Holy Ghost remains in us.  The unity of God and Man(meaning women as well).  Our children also represents this unity.  One of my goals in life is to recognize this truthly love and lovely truth.  This is the way which God speaks to us.  <br>
<br>
  As for the Bible, I think its very important.  Its a great tool for understanding our relationship with God.  I think a personal relationship with God is also very important.  But when discussing God with others, one should be more personal.  Humbility, humor a little more lay back and not so much on the offensive.  Its great that you have strong beliefs, but remember, those are not your inventions.  Have you ever seen somehting, told someone and they couldn't see it, so then you stand next to them in an effort to point your finger to guide their line of sight?  Have you ever noticed that it rarely works?  We end up pointing from our own perspective no matter how empathetic towards the other person.  Try to be more humble and a little less threatening when speaking of God.  Let your listener know that you are open-minded and claim to be imperfect so they will be open-minded and not threatened by some sort of goal that isn't in their sight.<br>
<br>
